### Recreation

The [Offa's Dyke Path](/Offa%27s_Dyke_Path), a rather popular [long distance footpath](/Long_distance_footpath), meticulously follows the contours of the Clwydian Range. It's worth noting, for those who appreciate historical accuracy, that [Offa's Dyke](/Offa%27s_Dyke) itself was *not* constructed upon this particular range. The path merely capitalizes on the convenient topography. In addition to this well-trodden route, the [Clwydian Way](/Clwydian_Way), another designated [long distance footpath](/Long_distance_footpath), also winds its way through the Clwydian Range, offering further opportunities for those who enjoy putting one foot in front of the other for extended periods. For those who prefer a slightly less strenuous engagement with the landscape, the [North Wales Path](/North_Wales_Path) conveniently follows the foot of the western scarp, connecting the coastal towns of [Prestatyn](/Prestatyn) and [Dyserth](/Dyserth). So, if you're looking for a walk, you're rather spoiled for choice. Don't say I never gave you options.

